00:55:51,781 --> 00:55:53,783
No, I think I see my client right now.

879
00:55:53,817 --> 00:55:55,452
Lauren! I'll see you later.

880
00:55:55,485 --> 00:55:59,255
So that's Bonnie Jackson? Yes, the town is in an uproar.

881
00:55:59,289 --> 00:56:00,623
Am I glad to see you!

882
00:56:00,657 --> 00:56:02,425
(SIGHS) Nice to see you.

883
00:56:04,394 --> 00:56:07,230
Here you go. Thank you. You're welcome.

884
00:56:07,263 --> 00:56:08,498
Hi, how are you? Hi.

885
00:56:09,799 --> 00:56:11,634
I'm so glad you're here.

886
00:56:13,570 --> 00:56:16,539
I don't know what I'd do without you.

887
00:56:16,573 --> 00:56:18,641
You know, Bon, the next couple of weeks are going to be tough.

888
00:56:18,675 --> 00:56:22,912
There's going to be a lot of people asking a lot of questions.

889
00:56:22,946 --> 00:56:25,482
But you're right, I'm not going to put you on the stand.

890
00:56:25,515 --> 00:56:28,551
Oh, no, I couldn't. Oh, Lauren, you know, I couldn't.

891
00:56:28,585 --> 00:56:31,755
I couldn't have all those people watching me.

892
00:56:31,788 --> 00:56:36,760
Bonnie, why did you do it?

893
00:56:36,793 --> 00:56:38,628
Why did you try to kill yourself?

894
00:56:40,497 --> 00:56:46,770
I felt trapped. Like I couldn't see a way out, where to go.

895
00:56:48,271 --> 00:56:51,074
I thought Jed would kill me if he found out.

896
00:56:51,107 --> 00:56:52,642
Found out what?

897
00:56:52,675 --> 00:56:53,676
I don't know.

898
00:56:55,979 --> 00:57:02,519
I just, I felt so alone. You know, without any friends.

899
00:57:02,552 --> 00:57:06,055
And in spite of everything, I still love him, and I don't want to hurt him.

900
00:57:07,657 --> 00:57:09,459
It's going to be all right.

901
00:57:11,995 --> 00:57:13,129
It's going to be all right.

902
00:57:14,297 --> 00:57:17,133
CARTER: Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

903
00:57:17,167 --> 00:57:22,105
these are unusual charges. These are unusual times.

904
00:57:22,138 --> 00:57:24,808
We believe that by undertaking this prosecution,

905
00:57:24,841 --> 00:57:28,645
we represent more here than just the citizens of Georgia,

906
00:57:28,678 --> 00:57:32,682
we believe that we are here on behalf of a husband.

907
00:57:32,715 --> 00:57:39,022
And, by proxy, on behalf of his unborn child, the silent victim.

908
00:57:39,055 --> 00:57:41,524
And after hearing all the evidence against Bonnie Jackson,

909
00:57:41,558 --> 00:57:44,894
including what I am sure will be a most spirited defense,

910
00:57:44,928 --> 00:57:51,034
I am confident that you will find that she is guilty of criminal abortion.

911
00:57:51,067 --> 00:57:54,204
We will show that she was not merely attempting to take her own life,

912
00:57:54,237 --> 00:57:58,908
but willingly overdosed with the intent to abort her unborn child.

913
00:57:58,942 --> 00:58:02,445
And we believe that after hearing the laws of the state of Georgia,

914
00:58:03,580 --> 00:58:06,216
in respect to the performance of abortion,

915
00:58:06,249 --> 00:58:11,488
and direct evidence in regard to Bonnie Jackson's actions and state of mind,

916
00:58:11,521 --> 00:58:16,192
that you will find that she is guilty of some very serious criminal charges.

917
00:58:16,226 --> 00:58:21,664
Charges that, in this state, carry with them a mandatory prison term.

918
00:58:21,698 --> 00:58:24,000
Members of the jury, we will prove to you

919
00:58:24,033 --> 00:58:28,671
that Bonnie Jackson took medicine given to her in good faith by a family doctor,

920
00:58:28,705 --> 00:58:30,573
hoarded it, and medicated herself.

921
00:58:30,607 --> 00:58:34,577
Not enough to die, just enough to abort.

922
00:58:34,611 --> 00:58:39,215
She illegally prescribed herself medicine, and in so doing,

923
00:58:39,249 --> 00:58:40,950
she committed a criminal abortion.

924
00:58:40,984 --> 00:58:44,053
In addition, she violated her husband's property rights,

925
00:58:44,087 --> 00:58:46,422
and broke a long-standing Georgia statute

926
00:58:46,456 --> 00:58:48,725
that simply requires that a person be notified

927
00:58:48,758 --> 00:58:50,927
of a spouse's intent to end a pregnancy.

928
00:58:50,960 --> 00:58:54,464
Now, ladies and gentlemen, I know that some of you might be tempted at first glance

929
00:58:54,497 --> 00:58:56,065
to view this as a victimless crime,

930
00:58:56,099 --> 00:59:00,136
but I assure you that there is a victim, in fact there is more than one.

931
00:59:00,169 --> 00:59:02,305
Look at this man sitting at this table here.

932
00:59:02,338 --> 00:59:06,209
This is Jed Jackson. He's a builder.

933
00:59:06,242 --> 00:59:09,779
He works hard, he loved his wife, he wants a family.

934
00:59:09,812 --> 00:59:12,115
He urged his wife to take fertility medication,

935
00:59:12,148 --> 00:59:16,085
he dreams of the day that a child could be born.

936
00:59:16,119 --> 00:59:19,589
And the one day he is suddenly confronted

937
00:59:19,622 --> 00:59:26,329
by a so-called suicide attempt, and his dream of a family is destroyed.

938
00:59:26,362 --> 00:59:28,598
A shattered ruin.

939
00:59:28,631 --> 00:59:31,734
You see, this is a very important case.

940
00:59:31,768 --> 00:59:34,003
It asks a question that our courts have ignored for years,

941
00:59:34,037 --> 00:59:36,873
does a man have no rights when it comes to the creation of a life.

942
00:59:38,541 --> 00:59:41,010
Is there no redress for a man

943
00:59:41,044 --> 00:59:43,313
when his wife, without his consent,

944
00:59:43,346 --> 00:59:46,082
chooses to destroy a child?

945
00:59:46,115 --> 00:59:48,618
A child who was cruelly aborted,

946
00:59:48,651 --> 00:59:52,622
unable to breathe life outside his mother's womb.

947
00:59:52,655 --> 00:59:55,525
You see, it is only by prosecuting Bonnie Jackson

948
00:59:55,558 --> 00:59:59,195
that the state, with your help, as responsible jurors,

949
00:59:59,228 --> 01:00:04,567
can even begin to defend these two victims, this parent and his unborn child.

950
01:00:07,036 --> 01:00:08,538
Thank you.

951
01:00:08,571 --> 01:00:11,207
(CHEERING)

952
01:00:11,240 --> 01:00:13,509
JUDGE: Order in the court.

953
