01:33:04,111 --> 01:33:06,247
And where did you reside before that date?

1513
01:33:06,280 --> 01:33:08,249
Why, we resided right here.

1514
01:33:08,282 --> 01:33:11,185
Mrs. Gordon and I lived just outside this town,

1515
01:33:11,218 --> 01:33:15,122
where we ran the Oaks Inn Motel, ran it for some 30-odd years.

1516
01:33:16,457 --> 01:33:19,427
What kind of people patronized that hotel?

1517
01:33:19,460 --> 01:33:20,695
Well...

1518
01:33:20,728 --> 01:33:23,698
In the early years, we had all kinds of people.

1519
01:33:23,731 --> 01:33:25,933
Traveling salesmen and the like.

1520
01:33:25,967 --> 01:33:28,369
Then, in later years,

1521
01:33:28,402 --> 01:33:31,472
more and more folks that just wanted to get away for a few hours.

1522
01:33:31,505 --> 01:33:33,140
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1523
01:33:35,076 --> 01:33:36,877
(GAVEL BANGING)

1524
01:33:36,911 --> 01:33:38,312
JUDGE: Proceed, Mr. Gordon.

1525
01:33:40,081 --> 01:33:43,351
Mrs. Gordon didn't like that. No, she didn't!

1526
01:33:43,384 --> 01:33:46,020
Then, last week,

1527
01:33:46,053 --> 01:33:48,856
we saw this Ms. Bonnie Jackson on the television,

1528
01:33:48,889 --> 01:33:52,293
and we knew that we must come back to Newnan to perform our duties

1529
01:33:52,326 --> 01:33:54,862
and testify for the sake of truth and justice.

1530
01:33:56,897 --> 01:33:58,699
(MURMURING)

1531
01:33:59,900 --> 01:34:04,872
Mr. Gordon. Can you identify the man who...

1532
01:34:04,905 --> 01:34:07,041
Stop it! ...who you saw at the motel with Mrs. Jackson?

1533
01:34:07,074 --> 01:34:08,876
That man. Objection!

1534
01:34:08,909 --> 01:34:10,845
In the third row, there, that black man.

1535
01:34:13,214 --> 01:34:16,617
(GAVEL BANGING) JUDGE: Order. Order in the court.

1536
01:34:18,719 --> 01:34:20,521
Return to your seats, please.

1537
01:34:20,554 --> 01:34:21,689
It's a trick.

1538
01:34:24,058 --> 01:34:26,260
Quiet, please.

1539
01:34:27,762 --> 01:34:28,929
Quiet!

1540
01:34:30,097 --> 01:34:31,766
Please continue, Mr. Gordon.

1541
01:34:31,799 --> 01:34:34,235
He and the accused, Mrs. Bonnie Jackson,

1542
01:34:34,268 --> 01:34:37,071
used to come to the motel in the afternoons.

1543
01:34:37,104 --> 01:34:40,775
It was the month of May, if I'm not mistaken.

1544
01:34:40,808 --> 01:34:42,777
No more! Your Honor, I want to testify!

1545
01:34:42,810 --> 01:34:44,245
Young lady, sit down!

1546
01:34:44,278 --> 01:34:47,214
Sit down! Sit down! No! You have ruined my life!

1547
01:34:47,248 --> 01:34:48,749
Your Honor, please let me testify!

1548
01:34:48,783 --> 01:34:50,051
Your Honor, my objection?

1549
01:34:50,084 --> 01:34:52,119
Your Honor, I also object.

1550
01:34:52,153 --> 01:34:55,790
Maybe we're onto something. Young lady, you may take the stand.

1551
01:35:09,937 --> 01:35:13,574
Raise your right hand. Place your left hand on the Bible.

1552
01:35:13,607 --> 01:35:16,110
State your name for the court.

1553
01:35:16,143 --> 01:35:17,645
I'm Mrs. Jed Jackson.

1554
01:35:20,347 --> 01:35:21,982
I'm Bonnie Jackson.

1555
01:35:22,016 --> 01:35:23,617
Do you swear to tell the truth,

1556
01:35:23,651 --> 01:35:26,821
the whole truth, and nothing but the truth, so help you God?

1557
01:35:26,854 --> 01:35:28,489
I do. Thank you.

1558
01:35:29,256 --> 01:35:30,925
(CAMERAS CLICKING)

1559
01:35:41,435 --> 01:35:42,803
I'm Bonnie Jackson.

1560
01:35:46,974 --> 01:35:51,011
And I knew that I was pregnant.

1561
01:35:51,045 --> 01:35:52,813
MAN 1: Murderer! She's a liar!

1562
01:35:52,847 --> 01:35:55,249
(CHATTERING)

1563
01:35:55,282 --> 01:35:56,317
MAN 2: Let her speak!

1564
01:35:57,318 --> 01:35:59,120
WOMAN: Go to hell!

1565
01:35:59,153 --> 01:36:00,721
MAN 3: You killed your child.

1566
01:36:01,689 --> 01:36:03,491
I couldn't tell you, Lauren.

1567
01:36:03,524 --> 01:36:05,459
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1568
01:36:06,160 --> 01:36:07,461
JED: Bonnie.

1569
01:36:08,329 --> 01:36:09,630
Jed, don't scream at me.

1570
01:36:09,663 --> 01:36:12,099
Bonnie! You, sir, sit down and be quiet...

1571
01:36:12,133 --> 01:36:13,767
Bonnie!

1572
01:36:13,801 --> 01:36:16,370
He never understood what I needed. He just screamed all the time.

1573
01:36:16,403 --> 01:36:17,638
Bonnie!

1574
01:36:17,671 --> 01:36:19,140
The only thing he wanted was a baby.

1575
01:36:19,173 --> 01:36:20,674
If you scream... Bonnie!

1576
01:36:20,708 --> 01:36:23,477
Bonnie! All he wanted was a baby.

1577
01:36:23,511 --> 01:36:25,646
(GAVEL BANGING) Bonnie!

1578
01:36:25,679 --> 01:36:28,983
JUDGE: That is enough! ...what I needed. And I needed something else.

1579
01:36:32,319 --> 01:36:36,557
And there was someone else,

1580
01:36:36,590 --> 01:36:41,595
who was gentle with me.

1581
01:36:45,699 --> 01:36:48,736
And so I went to that person.

1582
01:36:51,572 --> 01:36:53,240
(LAUGHING)

1583
01:37:20,100 --> 01:37:23,604
So I went to that person

1584
01:37:25,539 --> 01:37:27,741
'cause I was so lonely.

1585
01:37:31,278 --> 01:37:34,215
But I knew I couldn't have this child.

1586
01:37:36,083 --> 01:37:38,786
I knew that Jed would kill me

1587
01:37:38,819 --> 01:37:40,888
if he found out about this child.

1588
01:37:43,490 --> 01:37:46,460
And so I tried to kill myself

1589
01:37:48,929 --> 01:37:51,131
and my baby.

1590
01:37:51,165 --> 01:37:54,635
Come on, Jed. Let's sit down.

1591
01:37:55,836 --> 01:37:57,304
Come on, sit down.

1592
01:38:01,976 --> 01:38:06,747
Now, Bonnie, are you aware of the Georgia statute regarding criminal abortion?

1593
01:38:06,780 --> 01:38:07,948
No, sir.

1594
01:38:09,984 --> 01:38:11,785
Do you mind if I read it to you now?

1595
01:38:15,122 --> 01:38:18,058
"A person commits the offense of criminal abortion when he administers

1596
01:38:18,092 --> 01:38:21,762
"any medication, drugs, or other substance, whatever, to any woman,

1597
01:38:21,795 --> 01:38:25,132
"or when he uses any instrument or other means upon any woman,

1598
01:38:25,165 --> 01:38:28,869
"with intent to produce a miscarriage or abortion."

1599
01:38:29,970 --> 01:38:32,606
Section B.

1600
01:38:32,640 --> 01:38:34,842
"A person convicted of the offense of criminal abortion

1601
01:38:34,875 --> 01:38:40,814
"shall be punished by imprisonment of no less than one, nor more than 10, years."

1602
01:38:45,853 --> 01:38:50,324
Bonnie, in your own words, and for the record of this trial,

1603
01:38:50,357 --> 01:38:54,461
I must ask you to say whether anyone had any knowledge...

1604
01:38:54,495 --> 01:38:58,899
No. No, no one knew. It was my decision, mine alone.

1605
01:39:00,701 --> 01:39:03,337
So, the decision to end your life...

1606
01:39:03,370 --> 01:39:04,705
That was mine.

1607
01:39:06,573 --> 01:39:07,841
Your decision.

1608
01:39:07,875 --> 01:39:12,112
My decision. It's my life. It was my body.

1609
01:39:12,146 --> 01:39:13,781
And the life inside your body...

1610
01:39:13,814 --> 01:39:15,049
That was mine!

1611
01:39:16,884 --> 01:39:19,386
No woman could give that up easily.

1612
01:39:21,388 --> 01:39:26,393
But no one else should be able to make that decision for me.

1613
01:39:27,428 --> 01:39:28,429
No one.

1614
01:39:33,701 --> 01:39:34,702
Continue, Bonnie.

1615
01:39:37,237 --> 01:39:41,041
Do you think I could have given up my child that easily?

1616
01:39:41,075 --> 01:39:43,510
I was not ready to have a child.

1617
01:39:45,446 --> 01:39:48,382
I was not ready for Jed's child.

1618
01:39:48,415 --> 01:39:50,584
And I certainly could not have handled C. Ray's.

1619
01:39:52,553 --> 01:39:55,189
Maybe in another time or another place.

1620
01:39:57,257 --> 01:40:00,127
How could I have protected that child from my husband?

1621
01:40:01,428 --> 01:40:03,697
Or from the harshness of this town.

1622
01:40:07,935 --> 01:40:11,939
I didn't want to be pregnant then. It was an accident.

1623
01:40:16,143 --> 01:40:20,781
And I want children. I love children.

1624
01:40:23,584 --> 01:40:25,419
And I thought about having an abortion.

1625
01:40:28,455 --> 01:40:30,724
But I didn't want to do that, either.

1626
01:40:32,593 --> 01:40:36,096
It was the hardest decision I had to make in all my life.

1627
01:40:37,798 --> 01:40:41,902
So I decided to end it all because I didn't know what else to do.

1628
01:40:46,673 --> 01:40:49,243
Free Bonnie Jackson!

1629
01:40:49,276 --> 01:40:53,313
(CHANTING) Free Bonnie Jackson. Free Bonnie Jackson.

1630
01:40:53,347 --> 01:40:57,117
Free Bonnie Jackson. Free Bonnie Jackson.

1631
01:40:57,985 --> 01:41:00,587
(ALL SHOUTING)

1632
01:41:00,621 --> 01:41:02,589
(GAVEL BANGING) Free Bonnie Jackson.

1633
01:41:02,623 --> 01:41:05,626
You look at that face. You look at it!

1634
01:41:06,660 --> 01:41:09,596
Quiet! Quiet in the gallery.

1635
01:41:12,032 --> 01:41:15,469
Free Bonnie Jackson. Free Bonnie Jackson.

1636
01:41:22,876 --> 01:41:25,179
Let us have some respect in this court of law.

1637
01:41:32,953 --> 01:41:34,755
Silence! Quiet!

1638
01:41:34,788 --> 01:41:37,424
I will not tolerate this behavior in a court of law.

1639
01:41:37,458 --> 01:41:41,762
Will you control yourselves! Quiet. Silence!

1640
01:41:41,795 --> 01:41:45,833
Bailiff! I order this court cleared for the afternoon session,

1641
01:41:45,866 --> 01:41:48,335
at which time the jury will begin deliberation.

1642
01:41:48,368 --> 01:41:52,706
And I sincerely hope we will be able to conclude this case at the end of the day.

1643
01:41:52,739 --> 01:41:54,875
Court is adjourned!

1644
01:41:54,908 --> 01:41:57,511
REPORTER: Mr. Forest, Mr. Forest, do you think you will win this case?

1645
01:41:58,912 --> 01:42:01,148
(ALL SHOUTING)

1646
01:42:33,080 --> 01:42:34,081
Mr. Montgomery.

1647
01:42:35,382 --> 01:42:37,851
Mr. Montgomery, has the jury reached a verdict?

1648
01:42:38,752 --> 01:42:39,920
Yes, we have, Your Honor.

1649
01:42:55,369 --> 01:42:57,137
Will the defendant please rise.

1650
01:43:01,108 --> 01:43:03,644
Mr. Foreman, will you publish the verdict.

1651
01:43:08,081 --> 01:43:13,387
Count 1, as to criminal attempt to commit suicide,

1652
01:43:13,420 --> 01:43:16,690
we, the jury, find the defendant

1653
01:43:16,723 --> 01:43:17,724
not guilty.

1654
01:43:19,459 --> 01:43:23,764
Count 2, interference with husband's property rights,

1655
01:43:23,797 --> 01:43:26,767
we, the jury, find the defendant not guilty.

1656
01:43:29,102 --> 01:43:32,239
She's not her husband's property, she's community property now.

1657
01:43:32,272 --> 01:43:36,810
Count 3, failure to obtain spousal notification,

1658
01:43:36,843 --> 01:43:40,280
we, the jury, find the defendant not guilty.

1659
01:43:41,915 --> 01:43:42,916
(EXCLAIMS)

1660
01:43:44,284 --> 01:43:48,388
Count 4, unlicensed practice of medicine

1661
01:43:48,422 --> 01:43:54,595
to produce a criminal abortion, we, the jury, find the defendant

1662
01:43:55,662 --> 01:43:56,863
guilty.

1663
01:43:59,967 --> 01:44:04,338
Your Honor. Your Honor, I would like to be heard, please.

1664
01:44:04,371 --> 01:44:06,740
Sit down, Ms. McKinley. But something is wrong here.

1665
01:44:06,773 --> 01:44:10,477
Something is clearly wrong. I said, sit down, Ms. McKinley.

1666
01:44:10,510 --> 01:44:12,446
Does this mean that she goes off to jail?

1667
01:44:17,484 --> 01:44:22,089
Mrs. Jackson, you have been tried by a jury of your peers,

1668
01:44:22,122 --> 01:44:24,091
and they have made their judgment.

1669
01:44:24,124 --> 01:44:28,195
Before I pronounce sentencing, I want to say for the record

1670
01:44:28,228 --> 01:44:33,133
that I have lived uneasily with this case for some time.

1671
01:44:33,166 --> 01:44:38,538
Our country is so involved with this heated debate about abortion.

1672
01:44:38,572 --> 01:44:44,544
Ostensibly, the issue is about the question of when life begins and who should choose.

1673
01:44:44,578 --> 01:44:49,716
But the pro-lifers and the pro-choicers have been hurling every imaginable argument

1674
01:44:49,750 --> 01:44:54,888
at each other in an effort to gain new ground in their pitched battle.

1675
01:44:54,921 --> 01:44:59,893
They have thrown in morality issues, women's lib,

1676
01:44:59,926 --> 01:45:03,397
religion, family tradition and even racism.

1677
01:45:03,430 --> 01:45:08,235
And yet neither side has ever really listened to the other.

1678
01:45:08,268 --> 01:45:12,706
Tactics are escalating. The hatred intensifying.

1679
01:45:12,739 --> 01:45:16,877
We are steadily building toward another civil war.

1680
01:45:16,910 --> 01:45:22,015
Never has an issue so complicated and so sensitive

1681
01:45:22,049 --> 01:45:25,419
been so quickly politicized.

1682
01:45:25,452 --> 01:45:29,423
And never has the humanity behind such an issue

1683
01:45:29,456 --> 01:45:34,661
been so quickly forgotten, as though it were an unexploded landmine.

1684
01:45:34,695 --> 01:45:40,734
Now, as to the case before us, The State v. Bonnie Jackson,

1685
01:45:40,767 --> 01:45:43,704
Mrs. Jackson, I'm sure that you have come to see

1686
01:45:43,737 --> 01:45:46,740
that your misuse of prescribed medicine,

1687
01:45:46,773 --> 01:45:49,176
and of the confidence your doctor had in you,

1688
01:45:49,209 --> 01:45:51,745
caused a considerable amount of your turmoil.

1689
01:45:51,778 --> 01:45:55,048
Be that as it may, I want to give the both of you

1690
01:45:55,082 --> 01:45:57,884
an opportunity to rebuild your lives.

1691
01:45:57,918 --> 01:46:03,690
And with that in mind, I suspend sentence and fine you $1,000.

1692
01:46:03,724 --> 01:46:06,560
Yes! Judge, I got $1,000 right here. Jed, Jed.

1693
01:46:06,593 --> 01:46:08,528
Now, I can write you a check, and...

1694
01:46:08,562 --> 01:46:12,866
Sit down, young man, or I'll hold you in contempt of court.

1695
01:46:12,899 --> 01:46:15,202
Okay, okay.

1696
01:46:15,235 --> 01:46:16,570
I'll pay it later, then.

1697
01:46:17,604 --> 01:46:19,740
I just want to pay. Sit down.

1698
01:46:19,773 --> 01:46:24,544
Now, as to the performance of all other persons involved in this lawsuit,

1699
01:46:24,578 --> 01:46:30,484
and to the use of taxpayers' money herein, we can offer no opinion,

1700
01:46:30,517 --> 01:46:33,720
except that I can personally say that I have found these proceedings

1701
01:46:33,754 --> 01:46:36,823
to have been exploitive and outrageous.

1702
01:46:38,091 --> 01:46:41,161
Bonnie Jackson, you are free to leave.

1703
01:46:45,198 --> 01:46:47,567
This court is adjourned.

1704
01:46:47,601 --> 01:46:48,602
(GAVEL BANGS)

1705
01:46:51,638 --> 01:46:52,672
Thank you. Thank you.

1706
01:46:56,943 --> 01:47:00,614
Bonnie, I'll be outside. Maybe we can talk?

1707
01:47:03,116 --> 01:47:06,486
Our claim is that it was a great moral victory.

1708
01:47:06,520 --> 01:47:08,889
Yeah, that's our only chance to change the polls.

1709
01:47:09,790 --> 01:47:11,324
Are you listening to us?

1710
01:47:12,893 --> 01:47:14,628
Not anymore, I'm not.

1711
01:47:19,232 --> 01:47:21,668
Congratulations, Counselor.

1712
01:47:21,701 --> 01:47:23,703
Oh, come on, Lauren, be a sport.

1713
01:47:27,407 --> 01:47:28,642
See you around.

1714
01:47:43,089 --> 01:47:46,326
CROWD: (CHANTING DISTANTLY) Bonnie! Bonnie! Bonnie!

1715
01:47:49,529 --> 01:47:51,565
They're calling for us, Bonnie.

1716
01:47:51,598 --> 01:47:53,934
I'm finally doing something important for my life.

1717
01:47:55,335 --> 01:47:57,838
You have great plans.

1718
01:47:57,871 --> 01:48:01,908
I sure do, doll. I feel great. We won!

1719
01:48:04,211 --> 01:48:07,047
We didn't win anything. You won.

1720
01:48:08,548 --> 01:48:11,351
You loved it, didn't you?

1721
01:48:11,384 --> 01:48:15,989
All these bright lights, all this attention, all those people watching you.

1722
01:48:16,022 --> 01:48:19,192
You used me to get people to watch you!

1723
01:48:24,931 --> 01:48:29,803
Okay, maybe I did want some recognition.

1724
01:48:31,571 --> 01:48:33,707
Sure.

1725
01:48:33,740 --> 01:48:39,279
But I risked everything, my job, my future,

1726
01:48:41,815 --> 01:48:42,816
for you.

1727
01:48:45,085 --> 01:48:46,086
And we won!

1728
01:48:48,822 --> 01:48:50,423
Did we?

1729
01:48:50,457 --> 01:48:55,762
We sure did! We won a victory for women everywhere.

1730
01:48:58,932 --> 01:49:03,937
Lauren, do you really give a shit about women everywhere, or women anywhere?

1731
01:49:05,171 --> 01:49:07,374
You ungrateful bitch.

1732
01:49:07,407 --> 01:49:11,745
Ungrateful? For what? For becoming a goddamn sideshow?

1733
01:49:11,778 --> 01:49:14,114
I begged you to settle, but no, you wanted me parading around there.

1734
01:49:14,147 --> 01:49:17,550
Hold, hold, hold! I didn't know what would come out in this trial!

1735
01:49:17,584 --> 01:49:21,621
You didn't share with me the fact that you were balling C. Ray Thompson, thank you.

1736
01:49:23,690 --> 01:49:26,559
You're always the lawyer, you always know how to defend yourself.

1737
01:49:26,593 --> 01:49:28,295
Damn right, I'm a lawyer.

1738
01:49:28,328 --> 01:49:30,497
Next time you're on trial, why don't you get your dentist to help you!

1739
01:49:30,530 --> 01:49:33,733
Unless, of course, you're fucking him, too! Go to hell!

1740
01:49:33,767 --> 01:49:36,303
You ruined my life! Ruined your life?

1741
01:49:36,336 --> 01:49:40,140
Your life is what you make of it! Bonnie, you are a symbol.

1742
01:49:40,173 --> 01:49:42,208
I'm a symbol? I'm a symbol of what?

1743
01:49:43,510 --> 01:49:46,246
I wish... I wish I were dead!

1744
01:49:46,279 --> 01:49:50,750
Then take them. Take them! Take these pills.

1745
01:49:50,784 --> 01:49:55,288
Take them. After all you've been through, after all you could have been.

1746
01:49:56,990 --> 01:49:59,659
You had the courage for a moment.

1747
01:49:59,693 --> 01:50:01,861
But now you're looking for a new place to hide.

1748
01:50:01,895 --> 01:50:03,863
Shit. You're dead already.

1749
01:50:06,700 --> 01:50:08,802
If you don't grow, you die.

1750
01:50:11,638 --> 01:50:13,473
So get it over with!

1751
01:50:13,506 --> 01:50:17,243
Take the goddamn pills! We've got a prize outside, and I'm going to take it.

1752
01:50:24,918 --> 01:50:27,587
(DISTANT CHANTING)

1753
01:50:30,590 --> 01:50:33,560
You were worthless. Absolutely worthless.

1754
01:50:33,593 --> 01:50:37,130
How do you feel? I'm absolutely glad it's over with, that's how I feel.

1755
01:50:37,163 --> 01:50:39,199
Chrissy.

1756
01:50:39,232 --> 01:50:44,037
What are you doing here? I'm back with the media. My resignation is on your desk.

1757
01:50:44,070 --> 01:50:46,673
Well, I see. I hope you understand.

1758
01:50:46,706 --> 01:50:49,576
I hope I see you around, that's all. Sure.

1759
01:50:53,380 --> 01:50:58,118
CROWD: (CHANTING) Not the church, not the state, women should decide their fate.

1760
01:51:02,956 --> 01:51:06,760
REPORTER: Lauren, Lauren! Can we get some comments from you?

1761
01:51:06,793 --> 01:51:11,031
Congratulations, Lauren, we won. It's a great day for women.

1762
01:51:11,064 --> 01:51:14,034
Ms. McKinley, do you feel the women's rights movement has been vindicated?

1763
01:51:14,067 --> 01:51:16,069
REPORTER: Ms. McKinley, would you step up to our microphone?

1764
01:51:16,102 --> 01:51:17,637
Have all women been vindicated?

1765
01:51:17,670 --> 01:51:22,075
Yes. But at what cost to one woman? We stand here so deeply...

1766
01:51:22,108 --> 01:51:24,911
MAN 1: Here she is! Here she is!

1767
01:51:26,613 --> 01:51:28,948
MAN 2: You murdered, lady!

1768
01:51:28,982 --> 01:51:30,583
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

1769
01:51:31,885 --> 01:51:34,888
Lauren, I'm sorry.

1770
01:51:34,921 --> 01:51:35,922
I'm sorry.

1771
01:51:39,826 --> 01:51:42,395
Mrs. Jackson, Mrs. Jackson. Now that it's all over, how do you feel?

1772
01:51:42,429 --> 01:51:43,696
Are you going back to your husband?

1773
01:51:43,730 --> 01:51:44,764
Do you have any plans for the future?

1774
01:51:44,798 --> 01:51:45,965
Why don't you just leave her alone?

1775
01:51:45,999 --> 01:51:49,069
No, it's all right, it's all right.

1776
01:51:49,102 --> 01:51:51,404
You all can ask me any questions you want, I'm not afraid anymore.

1777
01:51:51,438 --> 01:51:53,339
(ALL CLAMORING)

1778
01:52:43,022 --> 01:52:49,028
Bonnie, I had a dream last night

1779
01:52:49,062 --> 01:52:51,564
and I dreamed that we were together.

1780
01:52:55,034 --> 01:52:56,736
I want to go home now.

1781
01:52:58,738 --> 01:53:03,176
I don't know, Jed. I need time.

1782
01:53:03,209 --> 01:53:07,614
Well, I think we can make it work out. I think I learned my lesson.

1783
01:53:07,647 --> 01:53:09,349
I need time, Jed.

